&lt;h3&gt;Erev Shavuot&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Candlelighting&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before dark, light candles. Recite the festival candle blessing and shehecheyanu (MT 384).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Ma&#039;ariv&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival evening service (MT 384) with appropriate additions for Shabbat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We recite an abbreviated Kabbalat Shabbat, consisting of Psalms 92 and 93. Some also recite a shortened form of L&#039;cha Dodi before Psalms 92 and 93.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival Amidah with appropriate additions for Shavuot and Shabbat (MT 468)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;During Dinner&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival evening Kiddush (MT 386).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many have the custom of eating dairy meals on Shavuot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add Ya&#039;aleh v&#039;Yavo for Shavuot and Harachaman for Yom Tov to Birkat Hamazon. Also include R&#039;tzei and Harachaman for Shabbat.&lt;/p&gt;
